<br>
If you want to be complete offensive, 50/50/28 WILL server you better.<br>
<br>
If you want to have the ability to deal good damage but don't want to give up too much defense (parry), 50/44/37 will do you better.<br>
<br>
44/44/43 is more of an all rounder template from its looks. You will be generally good with these skills, but no particular one will be your dominant spec. The only problem you'll (probably) have is unless you really like being well-rounded, you're going to wish you had more damage for when you arn't getting hit (remember parry doesn't block spells, and 70% of RvR is spells. You'll also be one of the last people to actually be hit unless you aim for a healer/caster, because meleers don't consider you a real threat.) Personally, I would miss Duel Shadows too much. It does more damage than amy (not much, but 3-4 more points is 3-4 more points I don't have to deal with <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
