<br>
But i have to qualify this with fact that i tend to do quite a bit of solo coin/salvage hunting. In that situation, the mobs are always facing you, and this style, even now, is amazing. Its damage sits between Amy. Slash and Diamond Slash, and actually out-damages that combo when End is taken into account. Two Dual Shadows (Pre 1.62, and after it's only going to give more) gives just a bit more the one Amy. Slash + Diamond Slash, for signifiganly less End usage. And against mobs that you have time to let the DoT bleed play out, it can actually be nice and add up.<br>
<br>
Speaking of bleeds, i have to point out one of my favorite things about Dual Shadows, and the bleed it gives. In RvR, any smart caster/healer that you charge will try to kite you (Run away full tilt, many times through the mass of friends to the safty in the back ranks) which is a smart thing to do, since if they just stand there, i'm going to chop them into little bits, fast. The thing is, you can usually get 1 or 2 swings/styles off before they turn tail to run, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>and</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> many times when you rush them, they are facing you. This is a perfect time to slap them once with Dual Shadows and get them bleeding all over the place. Even if they kite or you have to retreat back to your friends, 'tic-tic-tic-tic' they are still bleeding, and getting interupted. Thus, they may not be dead, but they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>can't</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> cast either. In RvR where 5-to-10 seconds of a caster not being able to cast can mean a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>lot</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, this little trick can be golden. &lt;Grins wickedly&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=adarmcneal@lighttanksofdaoc>Adar McNeal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(6/3/03 12:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hrm</span><hr size=1> Hello<br>
